      "message": "A neat property of the other formulas is that if you scale points by some scale, then\n\n  f\u0027 \u003d f * sqrt(scale)\n\nIntuitively this makes sense to me, and I\u0027m concerned that this current formula doesn\u0027t hold that property. Also, I was hoping to take advantage of that property in order to cache path data on GPU. If you just run all these formulas once and store the data on GPU, then every time you draw the path again you can just pull it back and for each curve:\n\n  numSegments \u003d cachedNumSegments * sqrt(matrixMaxScale);",
      "range": {
