      "message": "I tried this out locally but the \u0027vectorized matches reference impl\u0027 test was failing with tiny differences unless I also did the following:\n\n- Convert reference impl to also return sqrtf(denom / numer)\n- Remove use of grvx::fast_madd to compute the forward difference in the GrWangsFormula version\n\nWith both of those modifications the test passes again. WDYT? Here\u0027s some of the test failure messages to give you an idea of magnitude of difference:\n\n\t../../tests/WangsFormulaTest.cpp:463\t376988.156250 !\u003d 376988.125000 [WangsFormula_conic_matches_reference]: SkScalarNearlyEqual(ref_nsegs, nsegs, kTessellationTolerance)\n\t../../tests/WangsFormulaTest.cpp:463\t189629.453125 !\u003d 189629.437500 [WangsFormula_conic_matches_reference]: SkScalarNearlyEqual(ref_nsegs, nsegs, kTessellationTolerance)\n\t../../tests/WangsFormulaTest.cpp:463\t555373.312500 !\u003d 555373.250000 [WangsFormula_conic_matches_reference]: SkScalarNearlyEqual(ref_nsegs, nsegs, kTessellationTolerance)\n\t../../tests/WangsFormulaTest.cpp:463\t234587.390625 !\u003d 234587.406250 [WangsFormula_conic_matches_reference]: SkScalarNearlyEqual(ref_nsegs, nsegs, kTessellationTolerance)",
