      "side": 1,
      "message": "Isn\u0027t 2^log2(nsegs) \u003d\u003d nsegs?\n\nI think we need to scale the tolerance by the magnitude of the control points, not the number of segments. I don\u0027t remember what I assumed \"i\" and \"j\" meant in that previous comment, but looking again, it appears that \"for_random_beziers\" keeps the exponent to itself. It does, however, give back all the control points in the range [2^i, 2^(i+1)). So maybe we could try something like:\n\n  fabsf(pts[0].fX) * SK_ScalarNearlyZero\n\nOr even better:\n\n  maxMagnitude \u003d 0;\n  for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c 3; +i) {\n      maxMagnitude \u003d std::max(maxMagnitude, fabsf(pts[i].fX);\n      maxMagnitude \u003d std::max(maxMagnitude, fabsf(pts[i].fY);\n  }\n  threshold \u003d maxMagnitude * SK_ScalarNearlyZero;",
